The US Federal Reserve, the European Central Bank and the central banks of the United Kingdom, Switzerland and Canada have decided to fight together against the crisis in the financial markets.
More than $100 billion will enter the currency markets through auctions.
At these auctions, banks are auctioning off interest rates at which they are willing to lend to each other.
