"This move is designed to address the economy's biggest difficulties, namely the growing shortage of freely available capital that banks can lend," Bernard Baumohl of the consulting firm Economic Outlook Group wrote in a report for his clients.
"Coordinated central bank action has reduced the likelihood of a recession in the US from 65% to about 50%," Baumohl added in his report.
