600,000 people failed to change their driving licences
600,000 motorists missed the deadline to exchange their old licence, which expires at the end of the year.
Today is the last day when you can apply for an exchange so that the authorities can issue a new driving licence by the end of the year.
But the ministry does not fear that hundreds of thousands of drivers without valid driving licenses will take to the roads after the New Year.
According to the authorities, it is mainly those who no longer want to drive who have not changed their driving licences.
