In Prague, around 140,000 drivers have not yet exchanged their driving licences.
Issuing a new driving licence takes 20 days.
But it is possible to apply for the exhibition with a shortened period of five days.
In this case, however, the driver will have to pay 500 kroner.
Motorists who fail to make the required change by the end of the year and drive without a valid driving licence will face a fine from January.
The culprit pays a maximum of 2000 kronor.
However, the police can leave it at the transgression also with a reprimand.
In case of transgression, the penalty can rise to 2500 crowns.
According to previous information, even those who do not drive at all can be fined by the municipality.
