Ninety percent
Activity by Afghan insurgents has reached its highest level in five years, according to the U.S. Army.
The number of violent incidents has risen by 27 per cent compared to the previous year, and by as much as 60 per cent in the southern province of Helmand.
NATO countries have about 40,000 troops in Afghanistan, about a quarter of them in the southern territory.
According to the United States, however, the allies have reached an absolute limit in terms of the organisation and equipment of the units.
Specifically, they are calling for more helicopters, soldiers and experts to train Afghan units.
"We will have to think seriously about the concrete objectives for the next period and how we can achieve them," Gates said.
NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop made a similar statement today.
