After the American president, Abbas spoke and insisted that the coming negotiations be comprehensive and thorough, and provide a settlement on all points, enumerating Jerusalem, refugees, borders, colonies, water and security, among others.
When Olmert spoke, he pledged that the upcoming cease-fire negotiations would be conducted directly and without interruption, and that he would seek to bring them to an end before the end of 2008.
