Which insurance is best for me?
Car insurance, which covers a possible damage caused by the driver, involves a high cost, the amount of which in turn depends on various factors, such as age, gender, time of issue of the driving licence, marital status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
This is because it is even more difficult to find the right motor insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, let us be clear what we are dealing with here.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and a policyholder.
This agreement is set down in writing by means of an insurance contract, which stipulates that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and in return is obliged to submit the corresponding compensation amount in the event of damage.
The insurance premium is the price of insurance made up of several factors, including age, gender, time of issuance of the driving licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that higher premiums become due in the event of a higher risk of accidents.
This is why both over-25s and women have to pay less, as statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their prudence.
The same applies to married people, since, according to the statistics and therefore also according to the conviction of companies, they are more prone to accidents than single people.
The benefits attributed to the vehicle affect the frequency of driving and hence the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
Insurance companies must take a number of points into account when setting premiums.
For this reason, the driver also needs to study the situation thoroughly in order to select the car insurance that best suits his or her personal needs.
Here, we list the most important points to consider when choosing insurance, in order to be able to make not only a service-oriented, but also a price-oriented choice.
Those under the age of 25 face numerous obstacles when choosing low-cost insurance, such as poor driving experience and a young driver's license.
Even if it would be best to take out full comprehensive insurance for ideal cover, there are still cheaper alternatives.
Cautious drivers can choose a comprehensive comprehensive insurance with a deductible, so that the benefits of a comprehensive insurance are covered, but offered at a low price.
This type of contract implies that the customer must pay part of the amount incurred by the damage.
The amount is determined before the contract is concluded and based on the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher the lower the amount to be paid, explains Luis Noguera, principal representative of Spain at First Europa, an online insurance intermediary.
Another option is extended insurance, which insures the customer against external accident damage, but not against damage to the own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's some advice.
If you are under the age of 25, it is up to you to reduce the cost of insurance, so your credit will be increased by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction of the basic rate with the corresponding insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment implies an increase in said tariff.
The amount of the fines depends on the company and its earnings.
When the company has had a profitable year, it can afford to increase bonus payments, Noguera explains.
As soon as the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to conclude a contract, due to the fact that the accident rate decreases with increasing driving practice.
It is therefore best to opt for comprehensive insurance with a deductible.
Usually, young people are not able to take advantage of their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving, explains the Spanish head of the European company, adding that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice, after the fear of the beginner has been overcome.
However, for a married customer who does not have children, it is more advisable to take out comprehensive insurance; of course only if the financial situation of the person concerned allows it.
Insurers consider married couples with children to be the customers with the lowest accident rates, and their premiums are correspondingly low.
In this case, a fully comprehensive insurance with a deductible (for an amount of around 300 euros) would be the best option. In the event that you have received a high credit, an extended insurance policy is recommended, which does not take effect until the third year of the vehicle.
Overall, they drive more relaxed and have greater purchasing power, which allows them to pay a higher premium, Luis Noguera notes.
For retirees, it is advisable to take out comprehensive insurance with a deductible (for an amount of around 150 euros), or an extended insurance policy, which only starts with a sufficiently high credit.
Finally, it is important to note that car insurance is very important, not only because it protects the driver against possible accidental damage, but also because it involves high costs, which require a thorough selection that corresponds to our personal situation.
